dynMeta.chooseRuleConst:
During <color=#00a8ff>Kernel Locating</color>, you can <color=#00a8ff>choose and lock in</color> <color=#00a8ff>two 6-star operators</color> and <color=#00a8ff>three 5-star operators</color> to become rate-up operators.
While making your selection, you can further choose <color=#00a8ff>one 6-star operator</color> and <color=#00a8ff>one 5-star operator</color> to become <color=#00a8ff>available for exchange in the Store</color>. The chosen operators will become available in <color=#ffd800>[Distinctions]</color> and <color=#00a8ff>[Universal Certificates Exchange Area]</color>.
For the duration of the current Kernel Locating pool, the rate-up operators <color=#00a8ff>cannot be changed</color>.
dynMeta.homeDescConst: In Kernel Locating, the rate-up operators can be <color=#00a8ff>freely selected and locked in</color>! After selection, the rate-up operators <color=#00a8ff>cannot be changed</color>. A <color=#00a8ff>5-star</color> and above operator is guaranteed within the first 10 headhunting attempts!
dynMeta.star5ChooseRuleConst: In the current Kernel Locating, you can select <color=#00a8ff>3 operators</color> from the following 5-star operators, increasing their <color=#00a8ff>total appearance rate to be 50% of the 5-star rate</color>
dynMeta.star6ChooseRuleConst: In the current Kernel Locating, you can select <color=#00a8ff>2 operators</color> from the following 6-star operators, increasing their <color=#00a8ff>total appearance rate to be 50% of the 6-star rate</color>
